Korean media outlet YTN reported that during a press conference at the 5th Qatar Economic Forum (QEF) held in Doha, Qatar Tourism Chairman Alkarji stated:

"We tried to invite BTS last year as well, but it didn't happen because the main vocalist was serving in the military."

Jungkook is currently on hiatus, fulfilling his mandatory military service in the Army's 5th Infantry Division since 2023. Many fans reminisced about the time when the FIFA Chairman personally reached out to HYBE’s three main departments specifically to invite Jungkook to perform at the opening ceremony of the 2022 Qatar World Cup, where he sang his global hit "Dreamers."

ESTOY ACOSTUMBRADA A LOS GRANDES ESCENARION Q DIERON CADA UNO DE LOS CANTANTES DE BTS EN POCO O LARGO TIEMPO , TANTO COMO BTS, Y ES LA VERDAD, POR MAS Q ME QUIERAN TIRAR HATE, ESTA ESCENOGRAFIA PARECE EL SUPERBOWL DE RIHANA, LOS BAILARINES ESTAN VESTIDOS DE BLANCO EN LOS DOS, Y LA UNICA DIFERENCIA ES EL COLOR TOTAL EN SI, YA Q DE RIHANA ES ROJO Y EL DE JUNKOOK ES AZUL, PARECIERA Q ESTUVIERAN ENSEÑANDO AL MUNDO CUAL ES EL COLOR Q PERTENECE A LA IZQUIERDA Y A LA DERECHA, UNA ENSEÑANZA BASICA DE EDUCACION INICIAL, NO ME CONVENCIO ESTO, SERE SINCERA, PERO HASTA EL VIDEOCLIP DE DREAMERS ES MAS CREATIVO Q ESTA MEDIOCRIDAD, NO ME GUSTO PARA NADA, OBVIO Q ME GUSTO JUNKOOK Y LO UNICO BUENO Q HUBO FUE SU VOZ Y SU VESTIMENTA Y SU ENTREGA EN EL ESCENARIO Y CARISMA, EN EL SUPERBOWL DE RIHANA ME PASA LO MISMO , MEDIOCRE Y SIN CREATIVIDAD LO UNICO ME GUSTO ES SU VOZ Y SU VESTIMENTA, CARISMA Y PICARDIA Q SIEMPRE LE CARACTERIZA , PARA COLMO DE MALES, ESTOS EVENTOS TANTO LOS CUALES MENCIONO SON DEL MISMO AÑO, PARA Q ME ENTIENDAN HOY ESTAMOS 2025 Y EN LOS DOS EVENTOS Q MENCIONO SON DE 2 AÑOS ATRAS EXACTAMENTE , PERO ESO SI EN DIFERENTE FECHA, EN FIN , Q DIOS LOS BENDIGA A USTEDES TANTO A MI,  POR QUE SE QUE COMO ES ARMY Y EL HATE Q ME TOCARA, Y TAMBIEN DIOS  BENDIGA A RIHANA Y JK. Досужий ветер

знающим запах цветов и травы,

где-то живущих и тех, что мертвы.

с привкусом рек, синевы и хлебов,
мест, где пока не нашли самородок,
щедр и дорог, как боголюбовь.

Дух чужеземств и родимых величий,
шарм чужестранств и просторов морей
в сущности гостя в воздушном обличии,
в яви бесформенной в летней поре.

Акт водворённый и лён дуновенья
в каждом и каждой, как аура душ
в их озарении и испареньи,
явно подарочен, мил и досуж.

text: The Trophy was absolutely beautiful and stunning in this video’s display recording. Both teams actually deserved to be Champions Of The World of the World Cup 2022 of Qatar, not because of their goals or skills, it’s because of their passions, amazing performances and by far the greatest strategies that they’ve ever made, so far. I had an amazing feeling for both teams who scored goals in this World Cup Finals, especially, I was really impressed at Di Maria’s Goal. 🤗❤️‍🔥🫶 The Football was about to be an absolute sweat show football so far in this entire series. MBAPPÉ’s Comeback was absolutely lovely to see, especially his second goal what he scored + at 2 penalties, as well. 😍🤩🤗 But at Penalty Kicks, I felt that the time has to come, which I can tell that Argentina was about to make it to the Trophy of World Cup 2022 Qatar. I was really rooting for France too, cuz I had the strongest feeling that they would actually won this World Cup, but almost, because of their true, passioned strategies and determination in this Finals. 🇫🇷🤗🇦🇷 Argentina’s Goalkeeper was definitely a talented one. He was probably one of the best Goalkeepers, what I’ve seen so far at Poland and at Morocco, maybe, but can’t ignore France’s Goalkeeper, as well. 😍🫶❤️‍🔥

text: He had a shot in 2014, at 27, but the Germans were too resilient. He had another shot in 2015, but the Chileans, in their home country, held the Argentines and won on Penalties. However, in 2017,  in a period of darkness all around him, Edgardo Bauza, encouraged him to return back. 2018 may have been a bad year, and the same with 2019, but in 2021, he finally won a title with his country, beating their rivals Brazil. He won another in 2022, the Finallsima, against Italy at Wembley. And finally, in December, one man by the name of Gonzalo Montiel, secured a 3rd title but a final step. This made Messi an undisputed GOAT.

text:
আমি ছোটবেলা থেকেই মেসির একনিষ্ঠ ভক্ত। ফুটবল কী, তা জানার আগেই বড় ভাইদের মুখে শুনেছিলাম এক জাদুকরের নাম—লিওনেল মেসি। তারা বলত, এমন একজন খেলোয়াড় আছেন, যার সামনে কেউ টিকতে পারে না, যার পায়ের ছোঁয়ায় বল যেন জীবন্ত হয়ে ওঠে। তখনো বুঝতাম না, এই নামটাই একদিন আমার আবেগের সবচেয়ে গভীর জায়গাটা দখল করে নেবে।

২০১৪ বিশ্বকাপে জার্মানির বিপক্ষে আর্জেন্টিনার হার—সেটা শুধু একটা ম্যাচ ছিল না, সেটা ছিল স্বপ্নভঙ্গের এক রাত। সেদিন মনে হয়েছিল, যেন আমার হৃদয়ের এক টুকরো ভেঙে গেছে। আমি তখন ক্লাস ৩-এ পড়তাম, ফুটবলের নিয়মকানুন ঠিকমতো বুঝতাম না, কিন্তু মেসির চোখের জল বুঝতাম, তার কষ্ট অনুভব করতাম। সেদিন আমি কেঁদেছিলাম, ঠিক যেন আমার নিজের স্বপ্ন হারিয়ে গেছে।

তখন বন্ধুদের সঙ্গে খেলতে নামলে আমি সবসময় মেসি হতে চাইতাম। মনে হতো, যদি তার মতো একটুও খেলতে পারতাম, যদি তার মতো হতে পারতাম! সেই ছোট্ট আমি, যার হাতে তখনো বইয়ের ব্যাগের ভার, যার স্বপ্ন তখনো ফুটবলের মাঠে উড়ছিল, সে বুঝতে পারেনি—সময়ের স্রোত তাকে কোথায় নিয়ে যাবে।

আজ আমি HSC ২০২৫ পরীক্ষার্থী। সেই ছোট্ট আমিটা এখন বড় হয়ে গেছে, জীবন বদলে গেছে, কিন্তু মেসির প্রতি আমার আবেগ আজও একই রয়ে গেছে। এখনো যখন মেসির খেলা দেখি, মনে হয়—সময়টা থমকে গেছে, আমি এখনো সেই ছোট্ট ছেলেটাই আছি, যে মেসির হাসিতে হাসে, তার কষ্টে কাঁদে, যার হৃদয়ের প্রতিটি স্পন্দনে মেসির নাম বাজে।

২০১৪-র সেই হারের সাক্ষী ছিলাম, যেমন ২০২২-এ তার বিশ্বকাপ জয়েরও সাক্ষী হয়েছি। যেভাবে ছোটবেলায় তার কান্নায় কেঁদেছি, সেভাবেই তার হাতে বিশ্বকাপ দেখেও কেঁদেছি—তবে এবার আনন্দে। আজ আমি নিজেকে সৌভাগ্যবান মনে করি, কারণ আমি মেসির যুগের ভক্ত হতে পেরেছি, তার জাদুকরী ফুটবল দেখতে পেরেছি, ইতিহাসের অংশ হতে পেরেছি।

সময়ের পর সময় পেরিয়ে যাবে, নতুন তারকারা আসবে, কিন্তু মেসি... তিনি শুধু একজন ফুটবলার নন, তিনি এক অনুভূতি, এক অধ্যায়, যা কোনোদিন শেষ হবে না। ভবিষ্যতে হয়তো একদিন আমিও আমার সন্তানদের গল্প শোনাবো—একটা সময় ছিল, যখন মেসি নামের এক জাদুকর ছিলেন, যার পায়ের ছোঁয়ায় ফুটবল কথা বলত, যার ভালোবাসায় কোটি কোটি হৃদয় একসাথে স্পন্দিত হতো।

Korean media outlet YTN reported that during a press conference at the 5th Qatar Economic Forum (QEF) held in Doha, Qatar Tourism Chairman Alkarji stated:

"We tried to invite BTS last year as well, but it didn't happen because the main vocalist was serving in the military."

Jungkook is currently on hiatus, fulfilling his mandatory military service in the Army's 5th Infantry Division since 2023. Many fans reminisced about the time when the FIFA Chairman personally reached out to HYBE’s three main departments specifically to invite Jungkook to perform at the opening ceremony of the 2022 Qatar World Cup, where he sang his global hit "Dreamers."

text: The greatest final, yes, but not the greatest match ever, that remains the Italy/Germany semi final in 1970.  Had this final been settled with a fourth, (and the French nearly did get a winner) then this would have been both the greatest final and the greatest match.  Up to now the greatest final had been the Wembley story, not now.   1970 had the greatest game, save (Gordon Banks from Pele), tackle (Bobby Moore on Jairzinho), miss (twice - both by Pele), player (need you ask), goal (Carlos Alberto in the final), and team (need you ask), and will remain a yardstick by which all world cups will be measured.

text:
QATAR’S HOSTING OF THE WORLD CUP

 The first problem is the desire to join them in their play and amusement. A lifestyle foreign to Islam and bigger than just the game.

 Loyalty to Islam is replaced by loyalty to team or country and friendships and enmity is based on this rather than iman and kufr.

 The environment created is completely haraam from the kits worn to the mixing in the stands, the music, advertising and culture.

 Qatar cannot try to garnish the haraam with some ayaat and selective application of laws rooted in sharia and think that makes the event halaal.

 They desire the lifestyle of the kufaar, hanker after it, even bribe to get to host it and expose the Muslims in their lands to all the evil, but expect that islam “as a culture” should be respected on par with all other “cultures”- is Islam a culture? Is it equal to other religions or lifestyles? Is it not the truth? Or is their version the cultural one?

 They claim to be doing dawah bringing in Zakir Naik and adding ayaat to the proceedings- stopping for salaah etc- would it be ok to host the worlds biggest music festival or open a nightclub in order to give dawah to those that will attend. Supplying everything needed for the haraam but pretending that the true intention is to spread Islam- does that even make sense?

Allowing alcohol outside the stadium instead of inside- how is that not compromising deeni principles? 
 

Is it even appropriate to recite ayaat inbetween music, or have hadith on every corner when the entire event is an affront to Allah and his Rasool ‎ (ﷺ) .Right and wrong are no longer clear- everything is mixed up and given an Islamic flavor- far more dangerous than doing the wrong and seeing it for what it is. This is confusing the common Muslim.

 He is unwittingly supporting Qatar because he thinks they are standing up for the deen - but he forgets that the whole event that Qatar is hosting is haraam and what they seemed to be standing up for was compromised anyway. This has absolutely nothing to do with the deen. It is fasad. 

If you don’t accept that the game itself and its environment are wrong then you will not be able to see the bigger picture and how the deen of Allah is being sold for a paltry price.

 While we are busy playing footsie with the kufaar on the field they are bombing our brothers and sisters, children and parents in other parts of the world and legislating against Islam in their countries and muslim counties where their henchman dictators do it on their behalf.

But who wants to know about all that and how we should be fighting against the kufaar instead of playing with them and talking harmony- why look at our real obligation when we can enjoy being distracted by a game and live in an artificial reality created by them to keep us busy so we don’t realize what’s happening and fighting them (as we should be) is the furthest thing from our minds.

After all they even have Muslim prop players to soften our hearts and make us find deeni excuses to be involved in the religion of football - do we really believe they are there for dawah and that we have more impact on the kufaar then they have on us? When mo salah celebrates christmas or fondles with a model on gq magazine- who is influencing who- is he the da’ee we celebrate?

 The shaytaani symbolism are many and openly on show. Look at the arm stretching between the Morgan freeeman and the disabled hafidh imitating the “the creation of Adam” painting by Michaelangelo and recreating his role as “God” from the movie “Bruce Almighty” - with the kaafir above the muslim as his God- how symbolic. Look at the jinn mascot who openly talks about a different dimension that existed before man and the emphasis on Magic - the entire concept is from the occult and open to see. 

 But despite all the above which is clear and apparent, the ingrained love for soccer and our hearts attachment to their sport, their leagues, their brands , their celebrity- will not allow us to recognize the wrong and repent. Even if we are caught up, atleast to make tawbah. Instead we go into defence mode and blame the “backward” ulema because we find other ulema who are more “with it”, who endorse it and tell us it is ok. Beyond our infatuation with it, if we look deep into our hearts do we really think there is nothing wrong with the sport and everything that surrounds it? Is the real mufti (our heart) so consumed by the love of things of this dunya that it is no longer able to see clear haraam being masked with a veneer of halaal?

We have lost our way as an ummah and we desire to only follow those who will endorse our lifestyle , which is in effect the same as the lifestyle of the kufaar. Little separates us nowadays and we are lucky if we are eating and drinking halaal. The rest is the same. If there is nothing wrong with this and the ulema who rubber stamp it and participate in it are correct can you imagine if Nabi ‎ (ﷺ) and the sahabah were here today would they be attending the World Cup? do you think they would be encouraging inter faith or looking at ways to bridge the gap harmoniously between the Muslims and the kufaar? Is that the sunnah?

 Think deeply about it- not only in regard to the soccer but our entire lives- before dismissing those few ulema who are trying desperately to save us from the fire by warning us and encouraging us and those who are fighting the fight against kufr and assimilation. Who are standing up for the deen despite the harsh and negative responses they get. Not dissimilar to ambiya who kept reminding and warning their people. Even if you are not strong enough to fight for the deen atleast accept that wrong is wrong and right is right- so that you can atleast repent. Aspire to change and even if we are weak, stand for the right things - the only thing worth giving your life and wealth for- this gift of Imaan and the deen that our Nabi ‎ (ﷺ) took 23 difficult years to bring to us. Don’t throw it away because the lifestyle they sold you is now too ingrained in you to change. It’s never too late.

May Allah strengthen us all, grant us istiqamah on the Haq and guide us on the siraatul mustaqeem
Copied

text:
​@@abdulrehmaangaming4515QATAR’S HOSTING OF THE WORLD CUP

 The first problem is the desire to join them in their play and amusement. A lifestyle foreign to Islam and bigger than just the game.

 Loyalty to Islam is replaced by loyalty to team or country and friendships and enmity is based on this rather than iman and kufr.

 The environment created is completely haraam from the kits worn to the mixing in the stands, the music, advertising and culture.

 Qatar cannot try to garnish the haraam with some ayaat and selective application of laws rooted in sharia and think that makes the event halaal.

 They desire the lifestyle of the kufaar, hanker after it, even bribe to get to host it and expose the Muslims in their lands to all the evil, but expect that islam “as a culture” should be respected on par with all other “cultures”- is Islam a culture? Is it equal to other religions or lifestyles? Is it not the truth? Or is their version the cultural one?

 They claim to be doing dawah bringing in Zakir Naik and adding ayaat to the proceedings- stopping for salaah etc- would it be ok to host the worlds biggest music festival or open a nightclub in order to give dawah to those that will attend. Supplying everything needed for the haraam but pretending that the true intention is to spread Islam- does that even make sense?

Allowing alcohol outside the stadium instead of inside- how is that not compromising deeni principles? 
 

Is it even appropriate to recite ayaat inbetween music, or have hadith on every corner when the entire event is an affront to Allah and his Rasool ‎ (ﷺ) .Right and wrong are no longer clear- everything is mixed up and given an Islamic flavor- far more dangerous than doing the wrong and seeing it for what it is. This is confusing the common Muslim.

 He is unwittingly supporting Qatar because he thinks they are standing up for the deen - but he forgets that the whole event that Qatar is hosting is haraam and what they seemed to be standing up for was compromised anyway. This has absolutely nothing to do with the deen. It is fasad. 

If you don’t accept that the game itself and its environment are wrong then you will not be able to see the bigger picture and how the deen of Allah is being sold for a paltry price.

 While we are busy playing footsie with the kufaar on the field they are bombing our brothers and sisters, children and parents in other parts of the world and legislating against Islam in their countries and muslim counties where their henchman dictators do it on their behalf.

But who wants to know about all that and how we should be fighting against the kufaar instead of playing with them and talking harmony- why look at our real obligation when we can enjoy being distracted by a game and live in an artificial reality created by them to keep us busy so we don’t realize what’s happening and fighting them (as we should be) is the furthest thing from our minds.

After all they even have Muslim prop players to soften our hearts and make us find deeni excuses to be involved in the religion of football - do we really believe they are there for dawah and that we have more impact on the kufaar then they have on us? When mo salah celebrates christmas or fondles with a model on gq magazine- who is influencing who- is he the da’ee we celebrate?

 The shaytaani symbolism are many and openly on show. Look at the arm stretching between the Morgan freeeman and the disabled hafidh imitating the “the creation of Adam” painting by Michaelangelo and recreating his role as “God” from the movie “Bruce Almighty” - with the kaafir above the muslim as his God- how symbolic. Look at the jinn mascot who openly talks about a different dimension that existed before man and the emphasis on Magic - the entire concept is from the occult and open to see. 

 But despite all the above which is clear and apparent, the ingrained love for soccer and our hearts attachment to their sport, their leagues, their brands , their celebrity- will not allow us to recognize the wrong and repent. Even if we are caught up, atleast to make tawbah. Instead we go into defence mode and blame the “backward” ulema because we find other ulema who are more “with it”, who endorse it and tell us it is ok. Beyond our infatuation with it, if we look deep into our hearts do we really think there is nothing wrong with the sport and everything that surrounds it? Is the real mufti (our heart) so consumed by the love of things of this dunya that it is no longer able to see clear haraam being masked with a veneer of halaal?

We have lost our way as an ummah and we desire to only follow those who will endorse our lifestyle , which is in effect the same as the lifestyle of the kufaar. Little separates us nowadays and we are lucky if we are eating and drinking halaal. The rest is the same. If there is nothing wrong with this and the ulema who rubber stamp it and participate in it are correct can you imagine if Nabi ‎ (ﷺ) and the sahabah were here today would they be attending the World Cup? do you think they would be encouraging inter faith or looking at ways to bridge the gap harmoniously between the Muslims and the kufaar? Is that the sunnah?

 Think deeply about it- not only in regard to the soccer but our entire lives- before dismissing those few ulema who are trying desperately to save us from the fire by warning us and encouraging us and those who are fighting the fight against kufr and assimilation. Who are standing up for the deen despite the harsh and negative responses they get. Not dissimilar to ambiya who kept reminding and warning their people. Even if you are not strong enough to fight for the deen atleast accept that wrong is wrong and right is right- so that you can atleast repent. Aspire to change and even if we are weak, stand for the right things - the only thing worth giving your life and wealth for- this gift of Imaan and the deen that our Nabi ‎ (ﷺ) took 23 difficult years to bring to us. Don’t throw it away because the lifestyle they sold you is now too ingrained in you to change. It’s never too late.

May Allah strengthen us all, grant us istiqamah on the Haq and guide us on the siraatul mustaqeem
Copied

text:
- Los 3 "Goles" de Argentina anulados por el VAR por Posición Adelantada ante Arabia Saudita (Para posteriormente, darse a conocer que uno de esos 3 “goles” fue mal anulado).
-  La “Plancha” de Yasir Al-Shahrani (Arabia Saudita) a Nicolás Otamendi que no fue ni revisada por el VAR en el 62' (Infracción que hubiera dejado con uno menos a la selección árabe y que hubiera concebido un penal para la Argentina al darse la falta en el área Saudí).
- La Derrota de Argentina ante Arabia Saudita (Dejando a la Albiceleste al borde de la eliminación y acabando con un invicto de 36 partidos desde Julio del 2019).
- El Penal que Szczęsny (Polonia) le atajaría a Messi (Siendo el único penal que este erraría).
- La Mano de Keanu Baccus (Australia) en el 3’ al ras del área (Mano que no sería revisada por el VAR y que hubiera concebido un penal a la Argentina).
- El Gol de Craig Goodwin (Australia) en el 76’, producto de un desvió de un jugador argentino (Enzo Fernández).
- Las 2 Claras Ocasiones de Gol desperdiciadas por Lautaro Martínez contra Australia en el 88’ y 90’ + 3 (Ambas jugadas siendo asistidas por Messi).
- La Atajada del Dibu Martínez a Garang Kuol (Australia), en el 90’+6 (Atajada la cual, de no haberse dado, hubiera desencadenado una innecesaria prórroga).
- El Gol de Weghorst (Holanda) en el 90’ +10 (Literalmente, en el último minuto, gol que mando a la “Albiceleste” a la prorroga).
- Las Atajadas del Dibu Martínez a Van Dijk y Berghuis (Holanda) y el ´posterior fallo de Enzo Fernández en la tanda de penales.
- El Posible Penal de Mac Allister por “carga” desmedida de Upamecano (Francia) que ni revisaron en el 62’ (Penal que, posiblemente, hubiera definido el partido).
- La Posible Roja de Rabiot (Francia) por “llave” a De Paul (Sin intención de jugar la pelota) que ni revisaron en el 64’ (Roja que hubiera dejado a Francia con 10).
- El Repentino y Sorpresivo Empate de Francia en tan solo 3 MINUTOS con 2 Goles de Mbappe en el 79’ y 81’ (Goles que no llegaron en 86 minutos de Imposición Argentina y a menos de 20 minutos del Final).
- El “Hat Trick” de Mbappe (Francia) en la Final (Convirtiéndose en el Segundo Jugador en la Historia que marca 3 Goles en una Final de un Mundial, después de Geoff Hurst en Inglaterra 1966).
- La Atajada del Dibu Martínez a Kolo Muani (Francia) en un mano a mano en el 120’ + 2  (Atajada la cual, de no haberse concretado, Francia se hubiese consagrado TRICAMPEONA DEL MUNDO).
- La Atajada del Dibu Martínez a Kingsley Coman y el posterior fallo de Tchouaméni (Francia) en la tanda de penales.
- La Argentina del 2022 paso a ser parte de las contadas selecciones en la historia de los mundiales que hayan jugado 2 prorrogas y 2 tandas de penales en una misma edición (7 en Total).
- La “Albiceleste” se convirtió en la primera y única selección en la historia de los mundiales, a la cual, le pitan 2 penales en contra en una final del mundo (Y también, a la que le anotan 2 goles de penal en una Final - Qatar 2022).

text:
@@KenanLaudat-tp3bp That's what Wikipedia says...

"Association Football" (the actual name of the sport) was shortened by "Assoc -er" ("soccer").

It's a British shortened term...
author: @davepazz580

text:
​@davepazz580  I wasn't saying that wasn't the name. I was just confused about how you could get soccer from association football.
It makes more sense now, but it's still a bit confusing.
author: @KenanLaudat-tp3bp

text:
@@KenanLaudat-tp3bp From what I recall, there was a trend in Britain to shorten some words by adding an "-er" at the end of some words... so "breakfast" became "breakker".

So they took the "Association" and isolated the "socc" and added the "er" and it became soccer.

Funny thing is if you go back and watch some old British programs from the 60's or before then, they will say "soccer" when referring to the game.

text:
Why can’t it be called soccer?
For people who don’t know, soccer is a shortened form from “Association Football” which is the term England’s governing body coined in 1863 when they drew up the rules for the modern game of football.
Dozens of huge clubs around the world still acknowledge the Association part by having the AF suffix in their club name.
So why on earth is it so wrong to use the word “soccer”?

text:
Liberal hypocrisy
When England hosted the World Cup in 1966, homosexuality was still illegal, and remained so in Scotland until 1980 and in Northern Ireland until 1982. When the law was finally amended, it merely "decriminalised private homosexual acts between men aged over 21, while at the same time imposing heavier penalties on street offences". 

As for workers’ rights, ongoing discrimination against non-white workers was rampant, including in British trade unions. 
Britain maintained its colonial holdings across the globe, from the then defiant white settler-colony of Rhodesia to Hong Kong and the Malvinas (Falkland) Islands to what were yet recent crimes against the Kenyan people who had just obtained independence in 1963. They were of little concern to human rights defenders. 

Qatar itself was at the time under British colonial rule.

Britain then, as now, still had blasphemy laws and the Church of England remains its official religion. Still, it hosted the World Cup without complaint from Europe’s civil libertarians, least of all from Amnesty International.

In 1974, when West Germany hosted the World Cup, the population in that country was experiencing its latest wave of government repression. 

In 1972 the West German government began to purge "radicals" from the civil service (which then included 20 percent of the West German workforce). West German trade unions routinely expelled "activist" members. The Federal Office for the Protection of the Constitution investigated 2.5 million citizens. 

In fact, 800,000 applicants for civil service jobs were investigated regarding their “allegiance” to the constitution. A policy of blacklisting, or "Berufsverbot" - for signing petitions, joining demonstrations, etc - of those deemed guilty ensued. 


A crackdown on universities, dismissal of teachers, and “voluntary” withdrawals of “questionable” books by publishers was the order of the day. Whereas Nazi anti-homosexual laws, which remained on the books, were repealed in 1969, official anti-homosexual discrimination continued in the country until 2000.

West German racism against Turkish migrant labour was also rampant. Indeed, most of the leadership of West Germany’s Justice Ministry between 1949 and 1973 were former members of the Nazi party, including dozens of former paramilitary SA members. 
But West Germany hosted the World Cup without complaint from Europe’s civil libertarians, least of all Amnesty International (which was urged to intervene on behalf of the Baader-Meinhof prisoners who staged a hunger strike in German prisons, protesting against torture. Amnesty refused to adopt them, as allegations of torture, in Amnesty’s estimation, were not “justified”.)  

When the World Cup was held in the United States in 1994, half the US states had anti-sodomy and anti-homosexual laws, and the widely disseminated claim that Aids was a "gay disease" had not yet subsided. The country was proceeding at the time with its sanctions against Iraq, which led to the death of half a million Iraqi children. 

Police killing and beating of black men on the streets of US cities became a public scandal in 1991, when the video of police violence against Rodney King in Los Angeles went viral. This aside from the ongoing New Jim Crow system of incarcerating Black people in US prisons, to which the Bill Clinton administration contributed significantly; the use of prisoners as slave labour as permitted by the 13th amendment to the US constitution, and the ongoing violation of Native American rights. 

But the US hosted the World Cup without complaint from European and US civil libertarians, least of all Amnesty International (whose report that year criticised the death penalty, and police brutality, and the forcible return of Haitian refugees, but not anti-homosexual laws, let alone the abuse of migrant workers, etc).
